# DeScout — Hackathon & Programme Tracker

## What it is
A Flutter mobile app that aggregates remote, paid, Nigeria-eligible hackathons and open-source
fellowships (GSoC, Outreachy, LFX, Hyperledger, DoraHacks, etc.) into a single filtered,
notifiable directory. Exposes programme data as a public AGPL-licensed JSON/REST feed.

## Who it's for
Primary: Nigerian developers (18–35) hunting remote paid opportunities.
Cold-start community: TechCabal Slack, Forloop, DevCareer.

## Stack
- Flutter + Riverpod (state) + go_router (navigation)
- Supabase (Postgres + Auth + auto-REST API)
- Push: OneSignal (standard), UnifiedPush/ntfy (fdroid), huawei_push (huawei)
- Sentry (errors), Shorebird OTA (standard flavor only)
- GitHub Actions (CI/CD + ingestion cron), CodeMagic (iOS builds)

## Distribution — NOT Google Play
| Flavor     | Store / channel             | Push          | OTA        |
|------------|-----------------------------|---------------|------------|
| `standard` | APKPure, Uptodown           | OneSignal     | Shorebird  |
| `fdroid`   | F-Droid                     | UnifiedPush   | None       |
| `huawei`   | Huawei AppGallery           | huawei_push   | TBD        |

## Release plan
- **v0.1**: Browse + filter, Supabase auth, ~25 seed entries from internships.txt
- **v0.2**: Save/track, push notifications, iOS, F-Droid + Huawei APKs
- **v0.3**: Automated ingestion (Devpost RSS, DoraHacks API, MLH iCal, Playwright), admin review queue, in-app submission form
- **v0.4**: Public API docs, static JSON feed, web app (Cloudflare Pages), user_tags personalisation

## Hard constraints — never violate
1. Licence is AGPL-3.0. Every new Dart file gets the AGPL header (see conventions.mdc).
2. All `programmes` reads in the app MUST include `.eq('reviewed', true)`. Never show unreviewed entries.
3. Supabase service role key NEVER appears in Flutter code — cron scripts only.
4. All ThemeData decisions live in `lib/src/core/theme/app_theme.dart`. No inline ThemeData in widgets.
5. No business logic in `build()` methods. Providers own all state and async calls.

